Author: bluejam
Title: [ANN][ICO] FortKnoxster - Telegram on steroids. Sale 19 FEB. EARLY REGISTRATION
Body: Received an email from FortKnoxster 1h ago:  Dear community,  First of all, thanks to the thousands of contributors who joined our early-bird pre-sale, your support and interest has been truly overwhelming.  Following an unforeseeable demand for the FKX token, we hit the total FKX token cap on Thursday the 11th January 2018, which was nearly two months ahead of the planned ending of our public ICO.  The day before, when we realized that we were running low on tokens, we sent out a ‚Äúheads-up‚Äù e-mail to the community on the 10th of January 2018, explaining that if people were interested in contributing, then now was the time to contribute, in order to not miss-out. This resulted in a massive influx of contributors in a very short time span. At that time (Thursday afternoon CET) both the Ethereum and Bitcoin blockchains were extremely slow and therefore some contributions came in many hours later, making it very difficult for us to both control the maximum token cap and to block further contributions.  As all early-bird contributions (due to security reasons) were made to individual wallets (and not to a public crowd-sale smart contract), it made it even more challenging to stop the early-bird private pre-sale in ‚Äúreal time‚Äù.  In total, we raised 11 M USD from more than 2000 contributors ‚Äì distributed on 87.4 M FKX token - a result we are very satisfied with ‚Äì also measured in the light of our very generous bonus structure.   After going through all the contributions and the calculations (some BTC contributions came days after), we concluded that we had in excess of 10% more token contributions, than we originally planned.  This was due to the strong demand and the above-mentioned delays in the blockchains.  Our priority from day one has been to have a broad crowd-sale for our community. A strong, broad and committed community is crucial for our growth and awareness of the FortKnoxster platform. Also, we do not want to disappoint people, who contributed in good faith, by not allowing them to get their FKX tokens.  Based on this, we have implemented a slight increase in the token numbers, as described below to ensure maximum participation and to adjust for the delay in registering contributions.  We have added an adjustment of 11.11% to increase the amount of FKX tokens making a total of 150 M tokens (from 135 M) and 89.250 M tokens available for the crowd sale (up from 80.325 M). Please check our updated white-paper for more information.  The difference between the 89.250 M and 87.4 M (1.85 M) will be air-dropped freely to all existing contributors-as an extra gesture Airdropped tokens are distributed proportionally and have status as extra bonus tokens.  We hope our community understands and supports this slight change in our terms ‚Äì and again thank you for the overwhelming support you have shown to FortKnoxster.  Short Q and A: Q: I already contributed ‚Äì what shall I do now? A: Nothing-sit back and wait for the tokens to be distributed.  Q: When are the tokens distributed? A: Latest the 18th of February.  Q: Hmmmm; can I have my contribution refunded? A: Sure, please login in to dashboard (before January 30 at 9.00 AM CET) to see refund instructions.  Q: Is there any further news regarding exchanges or other developments? A: Yes, we will soon release some exciting news ‚Äì so stay tuned to our social media platforms.   Got Questions? Our team members are always available to answer your questions. Join our public channels on Telegram and follow us on Bitcointalk, Twitter, Facebook, Reddit, YouTube, Medium. Also, you can always get in touch with us directly via email at contact@fortknoxster.com.

Author: hufflepuff4life
Title: [ANN][ICO] FortKnoxster - Telegram on steroids. Sale 19 FEB. EARLY REGISTRATION
Body: Great questions. The FortKnoxster platform is an end-to-end encryption system where all files and communications are encrypted in the clients browser, before they are sent to our servers. Decryption of data is only possible for the intended recipients. Our unique crypto architecture is developed using the Web Crypto API, which is more efficient, than most other Javascript based crypto-libraries and leverages on the browser‚Äôs own crypto stack implementation. FortKnoxster does not have a public API description available. Everything is built on JSON API calls from the web and app clients. FKX has them defined/described internally. The team may consider exposing some of these APIs like the storage API in the future. Our DEMO is functional, but very much a DEMO as it's not utilizing the blockchain tech at this time. So very much in DEMO mode to give users an idea of what to expect. You can sign up for our DEMO on our website here: https://demo.fortknoxster.com/register Our whitepaper delves into the technical aspects of the platform and what to expect for when we fully launch:https://fortknoxster.com/FortKnoxster%20Whitepaper.pdf

Author: filsid
Title: [ANN][ICO] FortKnoxster - Telegram on steroids. Sale 19 FEB. EARLY REGISTRATION
Body: How does bitcoin work? I built an app to show you.  As Bitcoin rose to unprecedented levels, it caught my attention & curiosity. I wondered, how does bitcoin really work?  As I went down the blockchain rabbit hole, I found that many resources rarely go beyond the ‚Äúrevolutionary‚Äù, ‚Äúdistributed‚Äù and ‚Äúimmutable‚Äù dialogue. Many talk about the what, but not so much the why and how.  I resorted to reading technical papers and source code to uncover this black box. I started sharing what I learned by building apps that demonstrated the inner workings of the blockchain.  What I realized was bitcoin was just blockchain + transactions. This article will cover the transactions part of the equation. If you would like a refresher on blockchain, checkout Blockchain Demo or this article.  https://medium.freecodecamp.org/how-does-bitcoin-work-i-built-an-app-to-show-you-f9fcd50bdd0d

Author: hufflepuff4life
Title: [ANN][ICO] FortKnoxster - Telegram on steroids. Sale 19 FEB. EARLY REGISTRATION
Body: Thanks for the support! Fortknoxster is one of the few ICO's with a working product. However, the platform is still currently in demo mode. Here are some things we know:  1. Blockchain integration is in roadmap - at present the keypairs are stored on the server, the private keys encrypted with a derived key from the user‚Äôs password which is never sent to the server (FortKnoxster never has access to the private keys).  2. Group video call is disabled in demo.  3. Sign up in mobile apps is disabled and will be available in  January 2018.  4. Decentralized storage (and rewards for offering your space for FortKnoxster‚Äôs micro-files - which won‚Äôt ever reflect a whole file in one location, thereby ensuring security) is also on the roadmap. First version with all features is Q2, while many of the features are already done and working. Right now everything is hosted in Switzerland and all the storage is centralized, using distributed and high-performance data storage. File storage is, at present, end-to-end encrypted - like everything else in the platform. Eventually, with decentralized storage, there will be thousands of computers that are hosting pieces of the files that are encrypted anyhow - for further protection.  5. P2P calling, completely encrypted and between devices. It uses webrtc, supported by Firefox, Chrome and Opera. Webrtc is also consumed by the native apps. By default the protocol is end-to-end encrypted.  6. Signaling for audio and video calls is done on top of the end to end encryption that allows regular chat.

Author: jscholz
Title: [ANN][ICO] FortKnoxster - Telegram on steroids. Sale 19 FEB. EARLY REGISTRATION
Body: Hi there - Fortknoxster is free to use as well. There will be paid tiers for super users and enterprise etc, but Riot is the same in this regard. Its also important to note that Fortknoxsters primary focus is on privacy and security. Their slogan is "What happens on Fortknoxster stays on Fortknoxster". Riot seems to treat encryption as a secondary feature. It even shows on their website that some encryption is only in beta testing: "All files and data transferred over Riot can be encrypted end-to-end (currently in beta)"  The other key differences are that Fortknoxster allows users to get paid to store portions of encrypted files. So there is no need for users to run their own servers, its all stored in multiple back-up locations in the cloud.  In short: Fortknoxsters biggest focus is security and privacy E2E for email, video, file sharing, chat etc. Riot seems to be more focused on group collaboration with security as a secondary feature.

Author: h3xh3x
Title: [ANN][ICO] FortKnoxster - Telegram on steroids. Sale 19 FEB. EARLY REGISTRATION
Body: Hey folks,  I mentioned the demo for FortKnoxster and included a link to sign up above (https://demo.fortknoxster.com/register) - I wanted to follow that up with further information. When you sign into the demo platform, it tells you ‚ÄòPlease note: This is a demo and some features are limited or disabled.‚Äô I had a chat with the CTO and co-founder of FortKnoxster (on the platform - we tested both audio and video chat and the quality was outstanding!) and asked about what features are limited or missing. Here‚Äôs the details!  Blockchain integration is in roadmap - at present the keypairs are stored on the server, the private keys encrypted with a derived key from the user‚Äôs password which is never sent to the server (FortKnoxster never has access to the private keys).  Group video call is disabled in demo.   Sign up in mobile apps is disabled and will be avail. Jan 2018   Decentralized storage (and rewards for offering your space for FortKnoxster‚Äôs micro-files - which won‚Äôt ever reflect a whole file in one location, thereby ensuring security) is also on the roadmap. First version with all features is Q2, while many of the features are already done and working. Right now everything is hosted in Switzerland and all the storage is centralized, using distributed and high-performance data storage. File storage is, at present, end-to-end encrypted - like everything else in the platform. Eventually, with decentralized storage, there will be thousands of computers that are hosting pieces of the files that are encrypted anyhow - for further protection.  P2P calling works, and is completely encrypted and between devices. It uses webrtc, supported by Firefox, Chrome and Opera. Webrtc is also consumed by the native apps. By default the protocol is end-to-end encrypted. Further, signalling for audio and video calls is done on top of the end to end encryption that allows regular chat.  Thanks, and we hope to see you on FortKnoxster!  Remember, what happens in FortKnoxster, stays in FortKnoxster!
